  16 @attr.s
  17 class DependencyResolver(object):
  18     pinned_deps = attr.ib(default=attr.Factory(dict))
  19     #: A dictionary of abstract dependencies by name
  20     dep_dict = attr.ib(default=attr.Factory(dict))
  21     #: A dictionary of sets of version numbers that are valid for a candidate currently
  22     candidate_dict = attr.ib(default=attr.Factory(dict))
  23     #: A historical record of pins
  24     pin_history = attr.ib(default=attr.Factory(dict))
  25     #: Whether to allow prerelease dependencies
  26     allow_prereleases = attr.ib(default=False)
  27     #: Stores hashes for each dependency
  28     hashes = attr.ib(default=attr.Factory(dict))
  29     #: A hash cache
  30     hash_cache = attr.ib(default=attr.Factory(HashCache))
  31     #: A finder for searching the index
  32     finder = attr.ib(default=None)
  33     #: Whether to include hashes even from incompatible wheels
  34     include_incompatible_hashes = attr.ib(default=True)
  35     #: A cache for storing available canddiates when using all wheels
  36     _available_candidates_cache = attr.ib(default=attr.Factory(dict))

  38     @classmethod
  39     def create(cls, finder=None, allow_prereleases=False, get_all_hashes=True):
  40         if not finder:
  41             from .dependencies import get_finder
  42 
  43             finder_args = []
  44             if allow_prereleases:
  45                 finder_args.append("--pre")
  46             finder = get_finder(*finder_args)
  47         creation_kwargs = {
  48             "allow_prereleases": allow_prereleases,
  49             "include_incompatible_hashes": get_all_hashes,
  50             "finder": finder,
  51             "hash_cache": HashCache(),
  52         }
  53         resolver = cls(**creation_kwargs)
  54         return resolver

  56     @property
  57     def dependencies(self):
  58         return list(self.dep_dict.values())

  60     @property
  61     def resolution(self):
  62         return list(self.pinned_deps.values())

  64     def add_abstract_dep(self, dep):
  65         """Add an abstract dependency by either creating a new entry or
  66         merging with an old one.
  67 
  68         :param dep: An abstract dependency to add
  69         :type dep: :class:`~requirementslib.models.dependency.AbstractDependency`
  70         :raises ResolutionError: Raised when the given dependency is not compatible with
  71                                  an existing abstract dependency.
  72         """
  73 
  74         if dep.name in self.dep_dict:
  75             compatible_versions = self.dep_dict[dep.name].compatible_versions(dep)
  76             if compatible_versions:
  77                 self.candidate_dict[dep.name] = compatible_versions
  78                 self.dep_dict[dep.name] = self.dep_dict[dep.name].compatible_abstract_dep(
  79                     dep
  80                 )
  81             else:
  82                 raise ResolutionError
  83         else:
  84             self.candidate_dict[dep.name] = dep.version_set
  85             self.dep_dict[dep.name] = dep
  86 
  87     def pin_deps(self):
  88         """Pins the current abstract dependencies and adds them to the history dict.
  89 
  90         Adds any new dependencies to the abstract dependencies already present by
  91         merging them together to form new, compatible abstract dependencies.
  92         """
  93 
  94         for name in list(self.dep_dict.keys()):
  95             candidates = self.dep_dict[name].candidates[:]
  96             abs_dep = self.dep_dict[name]
  97             while candidates:
  98                 pin = candidates.pop()
  99                 # Move on from existing pins if the new pin isn't compatible
 100                 if name in self.pinned_deps:
 101                     if self.pinned_deps[name].editable:
 102                         continue
 103                     old_version = version_from_ireq(self.pinned_deps[name])
 104                     if not pin.editable:
 105                         new_version = version_from_ireq(pin)
 106                         if (
 107                             new_version != old_version
 108                             and new_version not in self.candidate_dict[name]
 109                         ):
 110                             continue
 111                 pin.parent = abs_dep.parent
 112                 pin_subdeps = self.dep_dict[name].get_deps(pin)
 113                 backup = self.dep_dict.copy(), self.candidate_dict.copy()
 114                 try:
 115                     for pin_dep in pin_subdeps:
 116                         self.add_abstract_dep(pin_dep)
 117                 except ResolutionError:
 118                     self.dep_dict, self.candidate_dict = backup
 119                     continue
 120                 else:
 121                     self.pinned_deps[name] = pin
 122                     break
 123 
 124     def resolve(self, root_nodes, max_rounds=20):
 125         """Resolves dependencies using a backtracking resolver and multiple endpoints.
 126 
 127         Note: this resolver caches aggressively.
 128         Runs for *max_rounds* or until any two pinning rounds yield the same outcome.
 129 
 130         :param root_nodes: A list of the root requirements.
 131         :type root_nodes: list[:class:`~requirementslib.models.requirements.Requirement`]
 132         :param max_rounds: The max number of resolution rounds, defaults to 20
 133         :param max_rounds: int, optional
 134         :raises RuntimeError: Raised when max rounds is exceeded without a resolution.
 135         """
 136         if self.dep_dict:
 137             raise RuntimeError("Do not use the same resolver more than once")
 138 
 139         if not self.hash_cache:
 140             self.hash_cache = HashCache()
 141 
 142         # Coerce input into AbstractDependency instances.
 143         # We accept str, Requirement, and AbstractDependency as input.
 144         from .dependencies import AbstractDependency
 145         from ..utils import log
 146 
 147         for dep in root_nodes:
 148             if isinstance(dep, six.string_types):
 149                 dep = AbstractDependency.from_string(dep)
 150             elif not isinstance(dep, AbstractDependency):
 151                 dep = AbstractDependency.from_requirement(dep)
 152             self.add_abstract_dep(dep)
 153 
 154         for round_ in range(max_rounds):
 155             self.pin_deps()
 156             self.pin_history[round_] = self.pinned_deps.copy()
 157 
 158             if round_ > 0:
 159                 previous_round = set(self.pin_history[round_ - 1].values())
 160                 current_values = set(self.pin_history[round_].values())
 161                 difference = current_values - previous_round
 162             else:
 163                 difference = set(self.pin_history[round_].values())
 164 
 165             log.debug("\n")
 166             log.debug("{:=^30}".format(" Round {0} ".format(round_)))
 167             log.debug("\n")
 168             if difference:
 169                 log.debug("New Packages: ")
 170                 for d in difference:
 171                     log.debug("{:>30}".format(format_requirement(d)))
 172             elif round_ >= 3:
 173                 log.debug("Stable Pins: ")
 174                 for d in current_values:
 175                     log.debug("{:>30}".format(format_requirement(d)))
 176                 return
 177             else:
 178                 log.debug("No New Packages.")
 179         # TODO: Raise a better error.
 180         raise RuntimeError("cannot resolve after {} rounds".format(max_rounds))
 181 
 182     def get_hashes(self):
 183         for dep in self.pinned_deps.values():
 184             if dep.name not in self.hashes:
 185                 self.hashes[dep.name] = self.get_hashes_for_one(dep)
 186         return self.hashes.copy()
 187 
 188     def get_hashes_for_one(self, ireq):
 189         if not self.finder:
 190             from .dependencies import get_finder
 191 
 192             finder_args = []
 193             if self.allow_prereleases:
 194                 finder_args.append("--pre")
 195             self.finder = get_finder(*finder_args)
 196 
 197         if ireq.editable:
 198             return set()
 199 
 200         from pip_shims import VcsSupport
 201 
 202         vcs = VcsSupport()
 203         if (
 204             ireq.link
 205             and ireq.link.scheme in vcs.all_schemes
 206             and "ssh" in ireq.link.scheme
 207         ):
 208             return set()
 209 
 210         if not is_pinned_requirement(ireq):
 211             raise TypeError("Expected pinned requirement, got {}".format(ireq))
 212 
 213         matching_candidates = set()
 214         with self.allow_all_wheels():
 215             from .dependencies import find_all_matches
 216 
 217             matching_candidates = find_all_matches(
 218                 self.finder, ireq, pre=self.allow_prereleases
 219             )
 220 
 221         return {
 222             self.hash_cache.get_hash(
 223                 getattr(candidate, "location", getattr(candidate, "link", None))
 224             )
 225             for candidate in matching_candidates
 226         }

 228     @contextmanager
 229     def allow_all_wheels(self):
 230         """
 231         Monkey patches pip.Wheel to allow wheels from all platforms and Python versions.
 232 
 233         This also saves the candidate cache and set a new one, or else the results from the
 234         previous non-patched calls will interfere.
 235         """
 236 
 237         def _wheel_supported(self, tags=None):
 238             # Ignore current platform. Support everything.
 239             return True
 240 
 241         def _wheel_support_index_min(self, tags=None):
 242             # All wheels are equal priority for sorting.
 243             return 0
 244 
 245         original_wheel_supported = Wheel.supported
 246         original_support_index_min = Wheel.support_index_min
 247 
 248         Wheel.supported = _wheel_supported
 249         Wheel.support_index_min = _wheel_support_index_min
 250 
 251         try:
 252             yield
 253         finally:
 254             Wheel.supported = original_wheel_supported
 255             Wheel.support_index_min = original_support_index_min
